(90, 'Paal Kesari Recipe - South Indian Style Milk Kesari', '1/2 cup Sooji (Semolina/ Rava),1/2 teaspoon Ghee - for roasting the rava,3 cups Milk,3/4 cup Sugar,5 Saffron strands - (lightly powdered using mortar and pestle),1 Cardamom (Elaichi) Pods/Seeds - crushed (optional),1 teaspoon Ghee,5 Cashew nuts,5 Raisins,', 35, 4, 'South Indian Recipes', 'Dessert', 'Vegetarian', 'To begin making the Paal Kesari Recipe, prepare all the ingredients and soak crushed saffron strands in a tablespoon of warm milk for 15-20 minutes (Soaking is optional for better infusion).Heat a Pan with ghee and roast the rava/semolina by continuously ', 'https://www.sharmispassions.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/12791217765_a5fdc623eb_o-445x500.jpg'),
